es.csic.iiia.nsm.net.norm

Class GeneralisationNetwork<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.net.norm.NormSynthesisNetwork<T>
      • es.csic.iiia.nsm.net.norm.GeneralisationNetwork<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NormativeNetwork, NormGroupNetwork

    public class GeneralisationNetwork<T>
extends NormSynthesisNetwork<T>
    A generalisation network is a norm synthesis network whose nodes stand for nodes and whose edges stand for generalisation relationships between nodes. Additionally, the network contains the following information about the nodes it contains:
    1. the state (whether active or inactive) of each node in the network;
    2. the utility of each node, which contains information about how the node performs to avoid conflicts with respect to the system node evaluation dimensions and goals; and
    3. the generalisation level of each node in the network, which stands for the height of the node in the generalisation graph
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"

      • getGeneralisationLevel

        public int getGeneralisationLevel(T node)
        Returns the generalisation level of a node in the network. The generalisation level indicates the position (i.e., height) of the node in the network. As an example, while a "leaf" node in the network has level 0, its immediate parent has level 1, and the parent of the parent has level 2
        Parameters:
        node - the node
        Returns:
        the generalisation level of the node

      • isRepresented

        public boolean isRepresented(T node)
        Returns true if one of the following conditions hold:
        1. the given norm is active in the network; or
        2. the given norm is inactive but some of its ancestors (the nodes that generalise and represent it) are active in the network
        Parameters:
        norm - the norm
        Returns:
        true if the norm is active in the network, or it is inactive but some of its ancestors are active in the network
